<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1756" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1756">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/78.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 108.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 4, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No.
                                415, of the 19th ultimo, forwarding a copy of a note and translation
                                from the Panaman Foreign Office on the subject of the demands made
                                by the United States based upon the Cocoa Grove riot of July 4,
                                1912.</p>
                            <p>In reply the Department refers you to its instructions No. 104, of
                                February 18 last, advising you of its views on the subject.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>